    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-12-24T10:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-12-24T10:45:00-05:00" n="240"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d240">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.01/35: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Beaulac</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-24T10:00:00-05:45"
                            >December 24, 1931—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>223. Department’s 217, December 20, 1 p.m.<note n="34" xml:id="d240fn34">See
                        footnote 29, <ref target="#pg_203">p. 203</ref>.</note>. The Minister for
                    Foreign Affairs has just informed me that the Government of Nicaragua has
                    decided not to recognize the present <hi rend="italic">de facto</hi> regime in
                    Salvador, in accordance with the clear terms of the Central American treaties of
                    1923. Repeated to San Salvador.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaulac</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
